   <dcterms:title>Account of George Peter for burial expenses, 1813-1814</dcterms:title>
   <dcterms:created>1813/1814</dcterms:created>
   <dcterms:description>Includes a $5 charge on 23 October 1813 for a coffin "for a black man." On 9 February 1814, Peter was charged $50.00 for a lined coffin covered with black cloth, among other expenses, possibly following the death of his first wife, Ann Plater Peter, or one of their young sons. Autograph document, 1 page. </dcterms:description>
